1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,333
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,333 --> 00:00:02,733
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:05,433
(Application for Confirmation
of Intent to Divorce by Mutual Agreement)

4
00:00:08,900 --> 00:00:10,100
(Episode 34)

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:17,400
Honey!

6
00:00:35,777 --> 00:00:36,877
Honey! Watch out!

7
00:00:49,694 --> 00:00:51,961
Honey! My goodness!

8
00:00:55,153 --> 00:00:56,753
Seong Jun! Honey!

9
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:58,480
Honey! Wake up!

10
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,900
No! Honey! Wake up! Help!

11
00:01:03,461 --> 00:01:05,761
Honey! Somebody help!

12
00:01:06,933 --> 00:01:08,933
(Emergency Medical Center)

13
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:12,700
What should I do?

14
00:01:13,927 --> 00:01:16,127
Male, age 59, collided with a motorcycle.

15
00:01:16,373 --> 00:01:18,833
No major external bleeding,
but decreased consciousness.

16
00:01:19,309 --> 00:01:21,500
Doctor, what's wrong with my husband?

17
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,499
Why won't he wake up?

18
00:01:23,499 --> 00:01:25,100
There doesn't appear to be
any major external injury,

19
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,600
but there is a possibility
of a brain hemorrhage.

20
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:28,633
We'll start with a CT scan first.

21
00:01:29,033 --> 00:01:30,033
A brain hemorrhage?

22
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:32,533
Ma'am, please go to admissions
and register first.

23
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:34,723
I need to see my husband wake up first.

24
00:01:34,723 --> 00:01:36,576
If you want the tests done quickly,
you need to hurry.

25
00:01:36,928 --> 00:01:39,085
- Let's move him.
- Okay.

26
00:01:49,656 --> 00:01:53,080
Honey, you can't leave like this.

27
00:01:53,853 --> 00:01:54,953
I was wrong.

28
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,877
Please stay alive, please.

29
00:02:00,656 --> 00:02:02,829
I can't live without you, so please...

30
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:06,717
I can't live without you either.

31
00:02:13,912 --> 00:02:14,912
Honey.

32
00:02:16,445 --> 00:02:17,545
What happened?

33
00:02:19,616 --> 00:02:23,221
Are you okay? I mean...

34
00:02:25,292 --> 00:02:26,292
Are you really okay?

35
00:02:29,553 --> 00:02:32,053
Fortunately,
the CT scan shows no brain hemorrhage.

36
00:02:32,504 --> 00:02:35,104
He lost consciousness temporarily
due to the shock of the accident.

37
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,000
It's a mild concussion.

38
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:40,293
A concussion?

39
00:02:40,718 --> 00:02:43,985
Yes. Nothing showed up
in the other neurological tests either.

40
00:02:45,572 --> 00:02:48,572
Thank you, doctor. Thank you so much.

41
00:02:49,061 --> 00:02:51,161
Please avoid strenuous activity
for about a week,

42
00:02:51,161 --> 00:02:52,661
and get plenty of rest.

43
00:02:53,192 --> 00:02:56,833
His arm just has a mild ligament strain
from the fall,

44
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,200
so it's nothing serious.

45
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,100
He can go after getting an IV.

46
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,700
Thank you.

47
00:03:12,035 --> 00:03:13,357
Did you mean what you said earlier?

48
00:03:13,907 --> 00:03:16,133
You really can't live without me?

49
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:17,845
Is this really the time to joke?

50
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,107
A joke? I'm asking seriously.

51
00:03:21,107 --> 00:03:23,963
Are you Superman or something?
Why would you jump in like that?

52
00:03:23,963 --> 00:03:25,787
What if something had happened to you?

53
00:03:25,787 --> 00:03:26,787
You...

54
00:03:27,555 --> 00:03:30,181
You were about to get hit by a motorcycle.
What was I supposed to do?

55
00:03:30,181 --> 00:03:33,485
Even so, do you have two lives?

56
00:03:33,688 --> 00:03:37,371
They said I'm fine. Stop being mad.

57
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,280
I really can't deal with you.

58
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:47,075
Honey, let's go home.

59
00:03:47,961 --> 00:03:49,061
You'll come with me, right?

60
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,781
I said I'm fine. You don't need to help.

61
00:03:59,848 --> 00:04:02,677
Your knife skills aren't bad.
Where did you learn that?

62
00:04:03,183 --> 00:04:05,783
Mother, I'm a former Marine, you know.

63
00:04:06,168 --> 00:04:08,763
I'm from the strongest First Division.

64
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,591
I was a cook. A cook!

65
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:15,037
What? Seriously...

66
00:04:15,325 --> 00:04:16,933
With that personality and that face,

67
00:04:17,312 --> 00:04:19,412
how did you end up
getting involved with Seung Ri?

68
00:04:20,337 --> 00:04:22,004
Let me give you a tip. Listen carefully.

69
00:04:22,723 --> 00:04:25,423
If you come on too strong,

70
00:04:25,948 --> 00:04:28,715
women tend to pull away more. Got it?

71
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:31,107
Then what should I do?

72
00:04:31,349 --> 00:04:32,979
Don't you know how to play hard to get?

73
00:04:32,979 --> 00:04:34,237
Right, playing hard to get.

74
00:04:34,816 --> 00:04:37,383
But didn't I tell you about this before?

75
00:04:37,624 --> 00:04:40,568
My nickname used to be Ten Minutes.

76
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,835
Back in the day, if I set my mind to it,

77
00:04:42,835 --> 00:04:46,088
I could win most women over
in ten minutes.

78
00:04:46,088 --> 00:04:48,051
That's how I got the nickname Ten Minutes.

79
00:04:48,156 --> 00:04:49,952
Ten Minutes, my foot.

80
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:52,392
You couldn't win Seung Ri over
in ten years.

81
00:04:53,072 --> 00:04:55,565
Change your nickname to Ten Years
starting today.

82
00:04:55,845 --> 00:04:57,557
- What? Ten years?
- Yeah.

83
00:04:57,739 --> 00:05:00,571
What's this warm mother-son vibe?

84
00:05:01,563 --> 00:05:02,733
How have you been?

85
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:04,488
How is it going
with your webtoon these days?

86
00:05:06,233 --> 00:05:07,323
I don't know.

87
00:05:08,688 --> 00:05:10,088
Nothing's really happening.

88
00:05:11,088 --> 00:05:14,188
Equipment matters for webtoon artists.

89
00:05:14,672 --> 00:05:16,605
Should I get you the latest tablet?

90
00:05:17,323 --> 00:05:20,490
Really? Get it for me. Get it!

91
00:05:21,359 --> 00:05:22,359
Seo Seung Wu.

92
00:05:24,177 --> 00:05:25,610
How could you ask that of a guest?

93
00:05:25,843 --> 00:05:28,411
A guest? That hurts, Mother.

94
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:30,701
You're a guest. A lifelong guest.

95
00:05:31,049 --> 00:05:32,560
Right, brother-in-law?

96
00:05:33,237 --> 00:05:34,368
Brother-in-law?

97
00:05:35,148 --> 00:05:37,608
Yeah, brother-in-law.
So, do you need some pocket money?

98
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
How much do you need?
How much would be enough?

99
00:05:40,449 --> 00:05:41,549
How much can you give?

100
00:05:43,272 --> 00:05:46,672
You guys are ridiculous.
The person involved doesn't even care.

101
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,429
Chief Ko? What are you doing here?

102
00:05:51,429 --> 00:05:53,656
Hey. Hello, Mr. Seo.

103
00:05:53,656 --> 00:05:56,845
Yes, I heard she invited you for lunch,
but I forgot.

104
00:05:57,229 --> 00:05:58,333
Lunch?

105
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,365
Go wash up. The food's almost ready.

106
00:06:00,637 --> 00:06:02,752
Mother,
should I julienne these carrots too?

107
00:06:03,369 --> 00:06:05,957
- What? Yes.
- Okay, just a moment.

108
00:06:11,253 --> 00:06:13,443
Those knife skills are impressive.

109
00:06:15,787 --> 00:06:16,987
You're good.

110
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:28,100
- Mom.
- What's with you?

111
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,400
Why are you only coming now?

112
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,449
Do you know how much I missed you?

113
00:06:32,449 --> 00:06:34,325
What's going on?

114
00:06:34,856 --> 00:06:38,208
Welcome back, Mom.
Thank you for coming back.

115
00:06:38,984 --> 00:06:41,347
Anyone would think this is a reunion
of a long-separated family.

116
00:06:41,347 --> 00:06:43,520
I can't breathe!

117
00:06:43,973 --> 00:06:46,640
Are you just going to stand there?
Sit down.

118
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:50,717
Dad, what happened to your arm?
It was fine when you left.

119
00:06:50,859 --> 00:06:53,608
Wait, are you hurt? What happened?

120
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:57,232
Did you do this to him, Mom?

121
00:06:57,232 --> 00:07:00,645
What are you saying?
I was so happy to see your mom...

122
00:07:00,645 --> 00:07:02,067
that I ran and tripped.

123
00:07:02,575 --> 00:07:04,075
They said I'll be fine in about a week.

124
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,171
You should've been more careful.

125
00:07:06,807 --> 00:07:09,707
Mom, why did you pack so much stuff
when you left?

126
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:14,296
What is this?
Were you preparing for the CSAT?

127
00:07:14,483 --> 00:07:17,168
I told you.
I'm definitely going to college.

128
00:07:17,816 --> 00:07:19,205
Yes, you should go.

129
00:07:19,792 --> 00:07:22,959
All right. Starting today,
leave math and science to me.

130
00:07:23,191 --> 00:07:25,291
I'll teach you properly,
like a top instructor.

131
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,280
But I'll charge tutoring fees.

132
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,995
Okay, I'll pay the tutoring fees,

133
00:07:28,995 --> 00:07:30,779
so you take responsibility
for Mom's math and science.

134
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:32,985
Then I'll take social studies.

135
00:07:33,867 --> 00:07:37,456
Yeah, that sounds good.
Then Eun Hyeong can take Korean.

136
00:07:37,781 --> 00:07:41,011
Right. With all these top instructors
lined up at home,

137
00:07:41,011 --> 00:07:42,712
I might end up at a top university.

138
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,227
I'll call Eun Hyeong
and tell him to come quickly.

139
00:07:45,227 --> 00:07:46,928
No need. Call him later for dinner.

140
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,605
I'll prepare some food and make lunch.

141
00:07:50,409 --> 00:07:52,096
I'll make lunch, Mom.

142
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:56,429
Why are you thinking about taking care
of everyone as soon as you get home?

143
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:59,757
Really? Min Ho did that well?

144
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:02,066
That's what I'm saying.

145
00:08:02,066 --> 00:08:05,733
The judges were practically blown away.

146
00:08:05,733 --> 00:08:08,312
Of course. He's my son.

147
00:08:08,656 --> 00:08:11,277
He's sharp because he takes after me.

148
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,317
But the problem is Father.

149
00:08:17,781 --> 00:08:20,437
Why? Is he on Gyeol's side?

150
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:24,096
It's not about sides.
He's trying to be fair,

151
00:08:24,325 --> 00:08:26,691
so he even included overseas experts
on the panel.

152
00:08:27,648 --> 00:08:31,253
But if something goes even slightly wrong,

153
00:08:31,253 --> 00:08:34,771
I can handle our executives,

154
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:39,064
but I can't influence
those outside judges.

155
00:08:39,064 --> 00:08:40,585
That's the catch.

156
00:08:40,585 --> 00:08:43,252
Did Gyeol do as well as Min Ho?

157
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:46,179
Well, it's not so much that he did well,

158
00:08:46,179 --> 00:08:49,019
but it felt like it aligned...

159
00:08:49,251 --> 00:08:50,704
with Father's intentions.

160
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:54,699
But it's not viable at all.

161
00:08:55,272 --> 00:08:56,972
There wasn't...

162
00:08:57,994 --> 00:08:59,955
Hey, Gyeol.

163
00:09:00,413 --> 00:09:03,355
It's the weekend.
Are you heading out somewhere?

164
00:09:03,493 --> 00:09:05,435
Yes, I'm going to the office for a bit.

165
00:09:05,597 --> 00:09:08,771
The office? Are you already preparing
for the second round?

166
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:12,595
No, I just have something
I couldn't finish yesterday.

167
00:09:12,595 --> 00:09:15,036
Hey, why are you so two-faced?

168
00:09:15,248 --> 00:09:17,725
You said you'd just stay
by your grandpa's side,

169
00:09:17,955 --> 00:09:20,445
but now you're going all in.

170
00:09:21,275 --> 00:09:24,715
Since I'm in the competition,
I think I should give it my best.

171
00:09:24,715 --> 00:09:26,696
That's exactly what I mean
by being two-faced.

172
00:09:27,344 --> 00:09:30,115
You acted as if you'd just take it easy
and go back to the U.S.

173
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:35,525
Mother,
did you just come back from the market?

174
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:38,277
Yong Man, what is that?

175
00:09:38,829 --> 00:09:40,733
Seaweed and dried pollack?

176
00:09:40,877 --> 00:09:42,539
Don't you know what day it is
the day after tomorrow?

177
00:09:42,648 --> 00:09:44,096
The day after tomorrow?

178
00:09:45,336 --> 00:09:46,995
Did you forget again?

179
00:09:47,175 --> 00:09:49,853
How can you forget this day every year?

180
00:09:50,526 --> 00:09:54,309
Right, the day after tomorrow
is Gyeol's father's memorial day.

181
00:09:55,832 --> 00:09:56,832
Are you going out?

182
00:09:57,037 --> 00:09:59,084
Eat lunch before you go.
I'll make it quickly.

183
00:09:59,355 --> 00:10:01,400
It's fine, Grandma. I'll eat outside.

184
00:10:01,645 --> 00:10:03,633
- I'll be back.
- Okay.

185
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:08,269
- That's heavy. Take it to the kitchen.
- Yes, Madam.

186
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:12,491
How long are we going to keep holding
that memorial at our house?

187
00:10:12,917 --> 00:10:14,499
Seriously...

188
00:10:14,499 --> 00:10:16,920
You know we can't help it
while Father is still alive.

189
00:10:17,025 --> 00:10:20,058
Well, this year is the last time
we hold that memorial anyway.

190
00:10:22,892 --> 00:10:24,659
I'll be in the study for a bit.

191
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:25,759
Why the study?

192
00:10:26,419 --> 00:10:29,400
Come play some screen golf with me today.

193
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:30,500
I feel stiff.

194
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:33,709
Didn't you say you were going to study?
Go study.

195
00:10:34,816 --> 00:10:35,832
Right.

196
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:38,784
J'aime beaucoup danser ces jours-ci.

197
00:10:38,784 --> 00:10:40,300
Merci, merci beaucoup.

198
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,900
That's right, I should study French.

199
00:10:52,256 --> 00:10:53,489
You were out here, Grandpa?

200
00:10:54,419 --> 00:10:56,859
Yes. Where are you going?

201
00:10:57,867 --> 00:10:59,100
I'm going to the office.

202
00:11:00,184 --> 00:11:01,389
You did well yesterday.

203
00:11:02,553 --> 00:11:03,664
Being in this condition,

204
00:11:04,472 --> 00:11:06,979
I've realized that, while having
a hospital nearby is important,

205
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:12,491
what matters most
is having someone beside you...

206
00:11:12,765 --> 00:11:14,811
to greet when you wake up in the morning.

207
00:11:17,024 --> 00:11:21,085
But I'm just one of many judges,

208
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:24,392
so I can't predict the result.

209
00:11:26,092 --> 00:11:27,959
If you're convinced it's a good idea,

210
00:11:28,748 --> 00:11:31,976
then make sure you can justify it
from a business standpoint.

211
00:11:32,293 --> 00:11:33,411
Yes, Grandpa.

212
00:11:34,969 --> 00:11:37,269
And that employee on your team.

213
00:11:37,967 --> 00:11:39,367
I thought I'd seen her somewhere before,

214
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,144
and it turns out she's that young woman...

215
00:11:41,293 --> 00:11:43,853
who was protesting alone
in front of the company not long ago.

216
00:11:44,296 --> 00:11:48,853
Yes, she's the developer
of the Joy program our company acquired.

217
00:11:49,392 --> 00:11:51,917
I found the program fits...

218
00:11:51,917 --> 00:11:53,381
the retirement community I have in mind,

219
00:11:53,675 --> 00:11:56,797
so I decided to let the original developer
keep improving it.

220
00:11:58,299 --> 00:12:01,703
Having capable people by your side...

221
00:12:01,705 --> 00:12:03,105
is also a skill.

222
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:06,811
Yes, I'll keep that in mind.
I'll be going now.

223
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:18,900
Manager Han.

224
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:23,915
His back still looks a bit lonely.

225
00:12:25,827 --> 00:12:27,227
You think so too, right?

226
00:12:29,837 --> 00:12:31,870
Your presentation yesterday
was impressive.

227
00:12:32,232 --> 00:12:35,245
I was the one presenting,
but it wasn't really my achievement alone.

228
00:12:35,768 --> 00:12:37,619
It was all thanks to our team's brain,
Seung Ri.

229
00:12:38,552 --> 00:12:41,925
By the way, when did you decide...

230
00:12:41,925 --> 00:12:43,639
to bring in the external panel of experts?

231
00:12:44,285 --> 00:12:45,395
A while ago.

232
00:12:46,269 --> 00:12:47,515
From the moment the race began,

233
00:12:48,064 --> 00:12:49,853
the Chairman instructed us to prepare it.

234
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:55,163
So you didn't tell Seung Ri
until now either?

235
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:58,324
You did the right thing.
Knowing it wouldn't have changed anything.

236
00:13:00,459 --> 00:13:03,171
Min Ho, what is it about Seo Seung Ri
that you like so much?

237
00:13:03,853 --> 00:13:06,789
She looks like she wouldn't bleed
even if pricked with a needle.

238
00:13:06,789 --> 00:13:08,733
She's cold and aloof to the core.

239
00:13:10,053 --> 00:13:11,986
That's her charm. Didn't you know?

240
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,920
I have something to take care of,
so I'll get going.

241
00:13:15,827 --> 00:13:18,968
We have a guest, and this is how you act?

242
00:13:19,193 --> 00:13:22,093
We already ate and had tea.
What's left to do?

243
00:13:22,459 --> 00:13:25,901
Really? I'll hang out a bit longer,
so you go ahead.

244
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,200
Okay.

245
00:13:29,633 --> 00:13:31,461
I have some documents to look over too.

246
00:13:31,461 --> 00:13:33,361
Chief Ko, take your time.

247
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:34,800
Yes, Mr. Seo.

248
00:13:39,912 --> 00:13:41,075
I'll see you later.

249
00:13:42,536 --> 00:13:44,963
What are you doing?
Aren't you going after her?

250
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:47,920
What? I came to see you today.

251
00:13:48,435 --> 00:13:51,268
Mother,
I want to see Seung Ri's childhood photos.

252
00:13:51,784 --> 00:13:53,059
Seung Ri's childhood photos?

253
00:13:59,673 --> 00:14:01,931
If you're convinced it's a good plan,

254
00:14:02,851 --> 00:14:06,051
then make sure you can justify it
from a business standpoint.

255
00:14:08,076 --> 00:14:09,343
Business viability...

256
00:14:22,563 --> 00:14:24,888
What would Dad have done
in a situation like this?

257
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Hi, Team Manager.

258
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:44,200
Right now?

259
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:47,600
Yes, there's something urgent
I need to discuss about the second round.

260
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:48,680
Can you make it?

261
00:14:49,101 --> 00:14:50,211
I'm not sure.

262
00:14:50,651 --> 00:14:53,429
We are having dinner together
as a family tonight,

263
00:14:53,429 --> 00:14:54,957
so I think I should help my mom.

264
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:58,707
- Your mother came back?
- Yes.

265
00:14:59,851 --> 00:15:03,365
That's good to hear.
All right, then let's talk later at work.

266
00:15:03,864 --> 00:15:05,264
Yes, I'm sorry.

267
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,875
Is there something urgent at work?
Why don't you go?

268
00:15:10,245 --> 00:15:12,381
No, you'll have a hard time...

269
00:15:12,381 --> 00:15:14,115
grocery shopping
and preparing everything alone.

270
00:15:14,241 --> 00:15:15,541
She's got me.

271
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:17,763
I'm not studying
for the civil service exam anymore,

272
00:15:17,763 --> 00:15:19,718
and I don't have to be secretive
around Mom, so I've got plenty of time.

273
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:22,565
I don't need anything.
I can handle it on my own.

274
00:15:23,011 --> 00:15:24,437
Eun Ae, you go to work,

275
00:15:24,437 --> 00:15:27,648
and Eun Nim, you go upstairs
and write your web novel or whatever.

276
00:15:27,648 --> 00:15:29,408
What are you talking about?

277
00:15:32,083 --> 00:15:35,480
It's been a while. Your youngest daughter
is going to be your dedicated assistant.

278
00:15:35,656 --> 00:15:38,221
Cho Eun Nim, you've grown up.

279
00:15:38,709 --> 00:15:41,901
Of course I have.
I had to after all the trouble I caused.

280
00:15:42,254 --> 00:15:43,254
Right, Mom?

281
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,501
I should leave home more often...

282
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:49,043
so every time I come back,
you grow up a bit more.

283
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:56,433
What are you doing?

284
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:59,563
Was my closet always this dull?

285
00:16:00,212 --> 00:16:02,212
There's nothing to wear.

286
00:16:03,993 --> 00:16:07,760
What is this?
You never cared about fashion,

287
00:16:08,062 --> 00:16:09,483
and suddenly,
you're complaining about clothes?

288
00:16:12,835 --> 00:16:14,669
Wait a second. Just wait.

289
00:16:16,161 --> 00:16:17,161
What is she up to?

290
00:16:19,824 --> 00:16:22,109
Does this suit me?

291
00:16:22,312 --> 00:16:24,612
Yes, it totally suits you.

292
00:16:25,299 --> 00:16:26,944
It feels a bit awkward.

293
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:28,177
No, it's pretty.

294
00:16:28,555 --> 00:16:30,693
Go now. Hurry up.

295
00:16:30,872 --> 00:16:33,488
But why are you so invested in my clothes?

296
00:16:33,488 --> 00:16:35,901
Why do you think?

297
00:16:36,203 --> 00:16:38,597
Please, just stop being single forever.

298
00:16:38,724 --> 00:16:41,099
It's not like I'm going on a date.

299
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:44,392
Our team is in emergency mode
for the second round.

300
00:16:44,392 --> 00:16:46,736
Exactly.

301
00:16:46,736 --> 00:16:50,488
So go handle that emergency. Go.

302
00:17:08,548 --> 00:17:10,381
To my beloved wife Yeon Ja.

303
00:17:12,128 --> 00:17:15,784
Thinking about it, over the past 35 years,

304
00:17:16,763 --> 00:17:19,629
you never left my side
for even a single day.

305
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:24,909
For the past few days without you,
after always sleeping,

306
00:17:25,892 --> 00:17:29,523
waking, eating, laughing,
and crying together,

307
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:33,181
it feels like I've lost everything.

308
00:17:33,437 --> 00:17:35,037
I feel so empty.

309
00:17:35,797 --> 00:17:37,364
You must've been so hurt.

310
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:40,264
You must've felt
such a deep sense of betrayal.

311
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,941
What drove you to leave home?

312
00:17:43,685 --> 00:17:45,672
From the moment I first met you,

313
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:50,400
I always wanted to be the best man
in the world for you.

314
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:55,117
Protecting you and the children,

315
00:17:55,117 --> 00:17:56,517
and making you happy...

316
00:17:56,979 --> 00:17:59,645
I thought those were both my duty
and my happiness.

317
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:03,933
But after losing my job
and stepping out into the world again,

318
00:18:04,525 --> 00:18:07,629
I realized there was nowhere left
that needed me.

319
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:09,840
I was afraid.

320
00:18:11,085 --> 00:18:12,818
I can still work.

321
00:18:13,293 --> 00:18:15,197
There's still so much left for me to do.

322
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,900
But most of all,
I couldn't bear to show you,

323
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:20,883
who trusted me with all your heart...

324
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:25,164
and worked so hard,

325
00:18:25,164 --> 00:18:27,664
how pathetic I'd become.

326
00:18:29,269 --> 00:18:32,056
Please don't ever think...

327
00:18:32,056 --> 00:18:33,637
that we didn't consider you family.

328
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:39,059
I know the deep pain you carry
in your heart,

329
00:18:39,955 --> 00:18:41,821
and I'm worried that...

330
00:18:41,821 --> 00:18:44,395
this situation has hurt you even more.

331
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:49,477
Honey, Kang Yeon Ja.

332
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:53,805
I, and we,

333
00:18:55,345 --> 00:18:57,032
cherish you deeply,

334
00:18:57,433 --> 00:18:59,603
more than words can express.

335
00:19:00,570 --> 00:19:02,144
I miss you, Kang Yeon Ja.

336
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:15,429
Hey, were you crying?

337
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:19,837
Was my letter that touching?

338
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:26,040
Do you think a few lines in a letter
can undo everything I've bottled up?

339
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:29,259
All right. From now on,

340
00:19:29,577 --> 00:19:32,410
I'll try harder
so you won't bottle things up again.

341
00:19:33,511 --> 00:19:36,035
I'm going grocery shopping.
You want anything?

342
00:19:36,616 --> 00:19:38,989
Then I'll go with you.
It'll be heavy to carry alone.

343
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:43,333
No thanks. You can't carry anything
with that cast on your arm.

344
00:19:47,584 --> 00:19:48,684
I knew it.

345
00:19:50,183 --> 00:19:51,783
I had a feeling you'd be here.

346
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,000
What are you doing here?

347
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:58,243
Did you forget?
We said we'd talk after the competition.

348
00:19:58,500 --> 00:19:59,500
Let's go outside.

349
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,550
What I'm about to say...

350
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:10,850
Gyeol, I'm sorry. Let me go first.

351
00:20:11,996 --> 00:20:13,669
You probably already know,

352
00:20:14,267 --> 00:20:15,757
but I still like you.

353
00:20:16,392 --> 00:20:19,344
That confession from ten years ago
is still valid.

354
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:25,885
My answer hasn't changed in ten years.

355
00:20:26,959 --> 00:20:27,959
I know.

356
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:31,267
I'm saying this
even though I know I'll be rejected again.

357
00:20:33,045 --> 00:20:35,563
Looking back, all this time I liked you,

358
00:20:35,891 --> 00:20:37,816
I never gave it my all.

359
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:42,856
Not long after I finally confessed,
you left,

360
00:20:43,319 --> 00:20:45,491
so there was nothing I could do
about my feelings.

361
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:46,900
Seung Ri.

362
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:51,563
When this project ends,
I'm going back to the U.S.

363
00:20:51,797 --> 00:20:55,645
Even so, I'll keep liking you
and wait for your heart to open.

364
00:20:56,893 --> 00:21:00,536
If you just accept my feelings,
it doesn't matter where you are.

365
00:21:00,932 --> 00:21:02,611
I'll go to you.

366
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:03,900
Seung Ri.

367
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:09,045
Right. Maybe this is an obsession.

368
00:21:10,502 --> 00:21:12,555
But I just can't stop my feelings.

369
00:21:13,664 --> 00:21:16,725
So this time, I'm going to give it my all.

370
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:20,264
That way, I won't have any regrets.

371
00:21:23,466 --> 00:21:24,666
Do you remember this watch?

372
00:21:25,096 --> 00:21:27,229
You gave it to me the day before the CSAT.

373
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:32,277
After you left,
I kept it in the drawer for ten years,

374
00:21:32,835 --> 00:21:34,917
but I took it out again
the day you came back.

375
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,600
That watch...

376
00:21:38,785 --> 00:21:39,893
I didn't give it to you.

377
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:43,100
What?

378
00:22:13,672 --> 00:22:16,381
Seung Ri, you've worked hard.

379
00:22:16,749 --> 00:22:18,504
Do well on the CSAT. From Gyeol.

380
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:21,888
Why is this card here?

381
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,533
(One day until the CSAT)

382
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:46,072
Sticky rice cake? Could it be Gyeol?

383
00:23:09,224 --> 00:23:12,139
This watch was definitely
with your card...

384
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:21,700
Who is this from?

385
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,800
(Seung Ri, you've worked hard.
Do well on the CSAT. From Gyeol)

386
00:23:31,053 --> 00:23:32,133
Gyeol...

387
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:58,571
Seo Seung Ri, all this time,

388
00:23:59,837 --> 00:24:01,744
you thought that watch
was a gift from Gyeol?

389
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,367
- What are you doing, brother-in-law?
- Nothing.

390
00:24:04,367 --> 00:24:05,408
You said we'd go look at tablets.

391
00:24:05,408 --> 00:24:06,595
- Come on.
- Yeah, let's go.

392
00:24:22,637 --> 00:24:25,149
Where did he go?
Did he go out for some air?

393
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,131
That watch...

394
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,216
It doesn't matter who gave it to me.

395
00:24:32,925 --> 00:24:35,653
What matters isn't the past,
but how I feel now.

396
00:24:37,700 --> 00:24:40,883
My love for you hasn't changed since then.

397
00:24:41,399 --> 00:24:43,811
No,
it's even deeper and more desperate now.

398
00:24:44,856 --> 00:24:48,408
I don't have the capacity
to love or accept anyone.

399
00:24:50,299 --> 00:24:51,299
What about Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

400
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:56,045
Do you feel the same way about her
as you do about me?

401
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:08,280
You can't answer, can you?

402
00:25:08,976 --> 00:25:11,633
You don't even understand
your own feelings right now.

403
00:25:13,317 --> 00:25:16,371
That's okay.
I understand my feelings perfectly.

404
00:25:19,067 --> 00:25:23,379
Just stay where you are, as you are.

405
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,700
(TF Two Team Manager, Ko Gyeol)

406
00:25:43,453 --> 00:25:44,553
Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

407
00:26:02,216 --> 00:26:04,603
Why did I run away?

408
00:26:05,328 --> 00:26:07,931
It's not like I didn't know
that Manager Seo liked Team Manager Ko.

409
00:26:14,733 --> 00:26:17,053
Thanks to you, Mom came back,

410
00:26:17,410 --> 00:26:19,624
and our team's presentation went well.

411
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:25,368
It's okay. Everything will work out.

412
00:26:36,288 --> 00:26:37,288
My goodness!

413
00:26:41,149 --> 00:26:43,275
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm okay.

414
00:26:46,377 --> 00:26:48,048
You call that okay?

415
00:26:56,476 --> 00:26:57,543
That must hurt.

416
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:12,233
You're so careless.

417
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:16,859
Why did you suddenly show up like that?

418
00:27:17,089 --> 00:27:18,555
Do you know how startled I was?

419
00:27:31,100 --> 00:27:33,459
What's wrong?

420
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:06,433
(Our Happy Days)

421
00:28:06,433 --> 00:28:09,555
Could your team manager
be the one you met 25 years ago?

422
00:28:09,555 --> 00:28:12,469
That brave and charming first love?

423
00:28:12,469 --> 00:28:13,960
You like him, don't you?

424
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,923
Hey, don't say something so ridiculous.

425
00:28:15,923 --> 00:28:17,957
You and that team manager
have already started something.

426
00:28:17,957 --> 00:28:19,371
Is it the Team Manager's birthday today?

427
00:28:19,371 --> 00:28:22,200
Mother,
how is Gyeol supposed to eat seaweed soup?

428
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,536
It's his father's memorial.

429
00:28:23,536 --> 00:28:25,499
What? At Gyeol's father's columbarium?

430
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:27,100
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
